        'title' => 'Bani Pangasinan: Surip Beach and the Quiet West Coast',
        'slug' => 'bani-pangasinan-surip-beach-quiet-west-coast',
        'excerpt' => 'Bani sits on the West Pangasinan coast between Alaminos and Bolinao. Here is the slow weekend plan for Surip Beach and the old town.',
        'content_html' => <<<'HTML'
<p>Bani is the small coastal town of western Pangasinan, sandwiched between Alaminos and Bolinao on the South China Sea coast. Most weekenders go straight to Hundred Islands or Patar Beach and skip Bani entirely, but the town has a calm white-sand beach, an old Spanish church, and a coastal road that does not pull tourists. This is a slow weekend plan for Surip Beach and the Bani town center.</p>
<p>The town sits about 30 minutes west of Alaminos along the coastal highway. Tara, here is the weekend by day.</p>
<h2>Day One: Surip Beach</h2>
<p>Surip Beach is the calmer alternative to Patar Beach in Bolinao, around 15 minutes by tricycle from the Bani town center. The sand is white and fine, the beach is around 800 meters long, and the water is calm with a gradual depth. No big resorts, just a few small cottages run by local families. Day-use fee is around 50 pesos.</p>
<p>The beach has a small rock formation at the southern end that you can walk across at low tide. Sunset faces west, around five thirty in the afternoon, and the sky turns deep orange across the South China Sea. Stay until dark if you want the quieter beach moment; the day visitors leave by five in the afternoon.</p>
<h2>Day One Afternoon: Bani Town Center</h2>
<p>The Bani church is the Saint Mary Magdalene Parish, built in the 19th century with a plain colonial facade and a single bell tower. The plaza in front is the town center and the locals gather in the late afternoon for chess and merienda. The public market is one block away and stays open until early afternoon.</p>
<p>Walk three blocks east from the plaza to the old municipal hall, a stone building from the early 20th century with a working clock tower. The streets around it have a few surviving bahay-na-bato houses, some still occupied, others slowly being converted to commercial use.</p>
<h2>Day Two: Coastal Loop</h2>
<p>Rent a bike or hire a tricycle for a coastal loop from Bani to Burgos and back. The route passes through small fishing villages, mangrove patches, and the Cape Bolinao headland from a distance. Around two and a half hours round trip with photo stops. The road is paved but narrow.</p>
<p>Stop at the Bani public beach near the boundary with Anda Pangasinan. The sand is grayer here and the locals use the beach for boat launches, but the western view across the bay toward Hundred Islands is a quiet morning scene.</p>
<h2>Getting There</h2>
<p>From Cubao or Pasay, Five Star or Victory Liner run buses to Alaminos. From Alaminos, take a jeepney bound for Bolinao and ask to be dropped at Bani town. Total travel time is around six hours. By car, NLEX to TPLEX to Urdaneta, then the coastal highway through Alaminos to Bani.</p>
<h2>Where to Eat</h2>
<p>The carinderias around the Bani plaza serve early breakfast from five in the morning. Bagoong-flavored bangus, dinengdeng with bagnet, and the local pinakbet are the regular orders. For sit-down meals, the eateries along the coastal road serve grilled tuna and fresh kinilaw.</p>
<h2>When to Go</h2>
<p>November through May is the dry window. June through October is the wet season and the West Pangasinan coast gets the southwest monsoon swells. Sundays during summer are busiest at Surip Beach, with around 200 visitors. Weekday mornings rarely have more than 30.</p>
<p>Bani is the calmer Pangasinan town that gives you the same west-coast feel as Bolinao without the weekend crowd. Walk the plaza, swim at Surip, and the trip stops feeling like a Hundred Islands detour.</p>
HTML,
        'meta_title' => 'Bani Pangasinan: Surip Beach and the Quiet West Coast | Resort Guru PH',
        'meta_description' => 'A slow Bani Pangasinan weekend covering Surip Beach, the old church, the coastal loop, and the West Pangasinan small-town pace. DIY notes.',
        'tags' => 'Pangasinan, Bani, Surip Beach, West Coast, Weekend',
