    // 17. DONSOL FIREFLY RIVER NIGHT
    // ------------------------------------------------------------------
    [
        'source_url' => 'https://www.escapemanila.com/2019/03/top-tourist-spots-in-sorsogon-and-how-to-get-there.html',
        'source_blog_name' => 'EscapeManila',
        'source_image_url' => null,
        'title' => 'Donsol Sorsogon: The Firefly River Night Cruise',
        'slug' => 'donsol-sorsogon-firefly-river-night-cruise',
        'excerpt' => 'Donsol is known for whale sharks but the Ogod River firefly cruise is the calm evening angle. Here is the diy plan for the night ride.',
        'content_html' => <<<'HTML'
<p>Donsol in Sorsogon is famous for the whale shark interaction during the day, but the town has a calmer evening attraction that fewer travelers schedule: the firefly cruise along the Ogod River. The river runs through a mangrove forest where the local fireflies congregate in the trees at dusk, and a slow paddle-banca cruise takes you under the canopy as the lights start to blink. This is the diy plan for the night cruise and a short coastal evening.</p>
<p>The cruise launches from the Donsol Visitor Center area. Tara, here is the evening by stop.</p>
<h2>Late Afternoon: Coast and Sunset</h2>
<p>Spend the late afternoon at the Donsol coast for the sunset before the cruise. The beach south of the visitor center is dark sand and shallow water, calm in the dry months. Locals gather for swimming and small picnics. Sunset faces west around five forty-five in the dry season and the sky turns deep orange across the Burias Pass.</p>
<p>Walk to the visitor center by six fifteen for the cruise check-in. The center has a small bantay-laot exhibit on whale sharks and mangrove conservation that is worth 15 minutes if you have not seen it during the day.</p>
<h2>The Firefly Cruise</h2>
<p>Cruises run in small paddle-bancas, around four to six passengers each. The boat operator is a local fisherman and the cruise lasts around 75 minutes one way. You launch around six thirty and paddle slowly upriver as the light fades. The mangrove forest closes around the banca and the river narrows to a tunnel of branches.</p>
<p>The fireflies start to appear around seven in the evening. The locals call them aninipot and they cluster in specific trees along the river, sometimes hundreds in a single canopy that look like Christmas lights. The boat stops near the brightest trees so you can watch without the banca movement disturbing the insects. Keep the flashlight off; the fireflies disappear under direct light.</p>
<h2>The Return Paddle</h2>
<p>The return paddle takes around 45 minutes downriver. By nine in the evening you are back at the visitor center. The cruise fee includes a guide and the boat rental; bring your own water and a light jacket. The river gets cool after dark, especially in the dry months.</p>
<h2>Donsol Town Center</h2>
<p>After the cruise, drive back to the town center for late dinner. The carinderias along the main road serve sinigang na bangus and grilled tilapia. The locals start to close by nine thirty so order before then.</p>
<h2>Getting There</h2>
<p>From Manila, take a Cagsawa Travel or DLTBCo bus to Legazpi, then a smaller bus or van to Donsol. Total travel time is around 11 hours. By plane, fly to Legazpi from Manila in one hour, then a van to Donsol in 90 minutes. Most weekenders combine the firefly cruise with the morning whale shark interaction.</p>
<h2>When to Go</h2>
<p>November through May is the dry window and the calmest for the river paddle. The firefly population is highest in the dry months. Avoid the wet season from June to October; the river runs faster and the mangrove canopy is harder to navigate after heavy rain. New moon nights have the best firefly visibility; bright moon nights wash out the lights.</p>
<p>The Donsol firefly cruise is the calmer evening angle to the standard whale shark trip. Combine the two and Donsol gives you a full day of wildlife encounters without the resort-package feel of other Sorsogon weekends.</p>
HTML,
        'meta_title' => 'Donsol Sorsogon: The Firefly River Night Cruise | Resort Guru PH',
        'meta_description' => 'A calm evening plan for Donsol Sorsogon covering the Ogod River firefly cruise, the mangrove canopy, the sunset coast, and dinner notes.',
        'tags' => 'Sorsogon, Donsol, Firefly, Night Cruise, Wildlife',
